									<div class="post-title fix">
										<h2>
											<a href="http://www.sourcememory.net/veleda/?p=168" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Nahua shamanic traditions III">Nahua shamanic traditions III</a>
										</h2>
																				<div class="metabar">
											<em>
												
																								<span class="sword">by</span> <span class="post-author vcard"><a href="http://www.sourcememory.net/veleda/?author=1">Veleda</a></span>

																								
																									<span class="sword">on</span> <abbr title="2011-04-24" class="published">April 24, 2011</abbr>
																								
																								&middot;												<a rel="nofollow" class="comments-num" href="http://www.sourcememory.net/veleda/?p=168#comments" title="View Comments">No Comments</a>
																								
																								
																																			</em>
										</div>
									</div>


								</div>
																		<div class="post-excerpt">
											<p>More excerpts from Brinton’s 1989 Nagualism (see previous posts), with my comments in italics&#8230; Fr Nicolas de Leon on the deep reverence for Fire: &#8220;If any of their old superstitions has remained more deeply rooted than another in the hearts of these Indians, both men and women, it is this about fire and its worship, [...]</p>
										</div>

																					<a class="continue_reading_link" href="http://www.sourcememory.net/veleda/?p=168" title="View Nahua shamanic traditions III">
